A scientific forum highlights progress in carbon sequestration, with experts showcasing real-world projects.
In Norway, a million tonnes of CO2 are stored annually beneath shale and mudstone.
A similar initiative in North America extracts CO2 from a coalgas plant and stores it in an underground chamber.
The focus is on reducing pollution from power stations burning oil, gas, and coal.
Efforts to cut carbon emissions by 60% by 2050 are crucial.
British Prime Minister Tony Blair prioritizes climate change at the G8 summit, while the US remains skeptical.
Collaboration and innovative technologies are key to combating global warming.
